Class StaffMenu

java.lang.Object
CAMs_App.boundary.StaffMenu
All Implemented Interfaces:
Menu
public class StaffMenu extends Object implements Menu
The StaffMenu implements the generic menu, Menu. It provides methods to print the main menu and viewing the application. The class uses StaffController to manage staff-related activities

  • Method Details

    • printMenu

      public void printMenu()
      The printMenu() method displays the menu options available for staff user. It prints staff menu options such as creating a new camp, viewing all camps, viewing camps created by the staff user, changing password and logging out.
      Specified by:
      printMenu in interface Menu

    • viewApp

      public void viewApp()
      The viewApp() method allows Staff to perform various actions such as

      • Creating a camp : Staff user will be navigated to StaffController.createCamp() method
      • Viewing all camps : Staff user will be navigated to StaffController.viewAllCamp() method
      • Viewing camps created by the staff member : Displays the camps made by Staff user StaffController.viewCreatedCamp(String). Staff user will be navigated to StaffCampMenu after entering a valid camp.
      • Changing password : Staff user changes password via UserController.changePassword().
      • Logging out : Staff user logs out from the system and returning to the MainMenu.

      Invalid inputs prompts the user to choose again.
      Specified by:
      viewApp in interface Menu
